To clear this level, you need to log in using an SSH private key.
There is a flaw in the login logic, but we can exploit a specific vulnerability by shrinking the terminal window. Making the screen smaller interrupts the login sequence, causing it to load incompletely.
Once the loading freezes, you can trick the system into launching 'vi' editor mode. From there, manually force the shell path to change, and then spawn a normal terminal command prompt.
After successfully breaking through, you will gain full access to the machine and secure the password.

